        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Some very rich people live in the lawlesss nooks and crannies of the world. Many of those rich people have families and you became quite rich by finding out just how much some of those family members were worth.  Sometimes Daddy thought you were bluffing and you buried a little corpse in an unmarked grave.  More often, Husband Dearest figured out that you were serioius and got his wife back none the worse for wear.  You were a professional in a very small trade full of amateurs. You never damaged the merchandise until the third refusal to pay, you never worked two jobs in a row in the same country, and you never went back on an agreement.\n\nOccasional, you took contract work, more for the variety than the pay.  Your last job for instance.  A drug war of some sort or another was heating up in Afghanistan, and one faction figured that their rivals would back off if the opposing leaders son was threatened.  The pay was good - heroin was better than cash in the places you traveled - and the job was challenging but not too dangerous.\n\nThe kidnapping itself went down smoothly.  You slipped pas the security in the drug lords compound, came in through the teenagers window while he was sleeping and hit him with a tranq dart.  Ten minutes later you were driving away.  An hour after that you were arirborne and en route to your drop site in Kashmir.\n\nThirty miles from the airstrip your target got up, walked to the cockpit and jabbed the dart into you neck. When you woke up your target was sitting on your chest with your gun stuck in your face.  He had been a tes, he explained and you had passed.  Now you got to work for him and his organization."
